
                                           Data Types
                                               |
                         -----------------------------------------------------------
             Primitive                                                             Non-primitive
               |                                                                       |
       Boolean              numeric Type                                      String, Array, etc....
                                  |
         |           Character          Integral Value
                        |
       boolean       char                    |
                                   Integer         floating
                                     |                 |
                       byte short  int long        float double


Boolean:
     it can have two values, true/false. the size of boolean depends on virtual machine.
     the default value for boolean is 'false'.

Byte:

    Data Type        syntax                 size                       value                       default value
    boolean       boolean booleanVar       Virtual Machine specific    true/false                   false
     byte         byte byteVar              8 bits                      -2pow7 to 2pow7              0
     short        short shortVar            16 bits                     -2pow15 to 2pow15            0
     int          int intvar                32bits                      -2pow31 to 2pow31            0
     long         long longVal              64bit                       -2pow63 to 2pow63            0
     float        float floatVar            32bit                        7 decimals                  0.0
     double       double doubleVar          64bit                        16 decimals                 0.0
     char         char charVar              2bytes                       /u000 to /ufff


Char:
  If we try to assign a number and print the char variable it prints the corresponding keystroke.
  ex: char ch1 = 65 // this will print A
  ex: char ch2 = 97 // this will print a
  ex: char ch2 = 'T' // this will print T

Java Casting:
    Widening casting:
     You assign a smaller data type to larger data type.
     ex:
         int i=100;
         long j = i;
   byte -> short ->int-> long -> float -> double

    Narrow casting:
     You assign a larger data type to smaller data type.
     ex:
         long i=100;
         int j = (int)i;
the reverse way of widening



     ex:
       12.123457


